## Alerting module

`internal/modules/alerting/` is **decomposed into five subpackages** (Phase 3 of 2026-04-17 audit). Each is a proper directory with its own `module.go`:

- `alerting/rules/` — `/alerts/rules/*`, mute, test, backtest, audit
- `alerting/incidents/` — `/alerts/incidents`, `/activity`, `/instances/:id/{ack,snooze}`
- `alerting/silences/` — `/alerts/silences/*`
- `alerting/slack/` — `/alerts/slack/test`, `/callback/slack`
- `alerting/engine/` — `registry.BackgroundRunner` wrapping the evaluator loop + dispatcher + outbox relay (no HTTP routes)

Plus existing `alerting/evaluators/` (condition evaluators), `alerting/channels/` (Slack delivery), `alerting/shared/` (Rule/Instance/Silence/AlertEvent types + DTOs + definition + statemachine + template + helpers — all shared across subpackages), and `alerting/factory/` (composes the five submodules into `[]registry.Module` for `modules_manifest.go`).

**Parent `alerting/` has NO .go files** — it is a pure directory container. All code lives in `shared/` or one of the five concern subpackages. Import graph is one-directional: factory → submodules; submodules → shared (+ rules for incidents/silences, + engine for slack). Modules 52 → 56.

- **Storage**: single MySQL table `observability.alerts` — rule config + per-instance runtime state + silences all live inline as JSON columns. Append-only ClickHouse `observability.alert_events` (MergeTree, `PARTITION BY toYYYYMM(ts) ORDER BY (team_id, alert_id, ts)`) holds audit + transition history.
- **Routes**: `POST/GET/PATCH/DELETE /alerts/rules[/:id]`, `POST /alerts/rules/:id/{mute,test,backtest}`, `GET /alerts/rules/:id/audit`, `GET /alerts/incidents`, `POST /alerts/instances/:id/{ack,snooze}`, `GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE /alerts/silences[/:id]`, `POST /alerts/callback/slack`.
- **Evaluator loop** (`service.go:EvaluatorLoop.run`): 30s tick → `ListEnabledRules` → for each rule call `evaluators.Registry.Get(rule.ConditionType).Evaluate()` → `Decide()` (pure state machine in `statemachine.go`; states `ok|no_data|warn|alert|muted`, honors `for_secs`/`recover_for_secs`/`no_data_secs`/`mute_until`/`snoozed_until`) → on transition write `alert_events`, enqueue to in-memory `Dispatcher` (with deploy correlation via `DeploysInRange`), persist `SaveRuleRuntime`.
- **Dispatcher** (`dispatcher.go`): worker goroutine consumes a bounded Go channel, de-duplicates via `alert_id:instance_key:transition_seq`, renders notification via `text/template` in `template.go`, posts to Slack webhook via `channels.Slack`. Failures append `dispatch_failed` events.
- **Evaluators** (`evaluators/`): `SLOBurnRate`, `ErrorRate` — both wrap the shared repository DataSource (`SLOErrorRate`, `ServiceErrorRate`, `ErrorRateHistorical`) so they hit `observability.spans` through the same root-span definition used by `overview/slo`. New condition types = new struct + `NewRegistry` entry; no schema change.
- **Backtest**: `backtest.go:RunBacktest` loops `Evaluator.EvaluateAt` across a historical range without persisting state or dispatching — powers `POST /alerts/rules/:id/backtest`.
- **Deploy correlation**: `deployments.Repository.GetDeploysInRange` returns all root-span deploy markers in [start,end] across services for a team; alerting calls it on every transition to attach `deploy_refs` to the event + dispatch payload.
- **Error codes**: `errorcode.AlertRuleNotFound`, `AlertRuleInvalidCondition`, `AlertInstanceNotFound`, `AlertChannelNotFound`, `AlertSilenceNotFound`.
- **Module wiring**: `alerting.NewModule(sqlDB, nativeQuerier, clickHouseConn, redisClient, getTenant, baseURL, maxEnabledRules)` — registered in `modules_manifest.go:configuredModules()`. `Start/Stop` fan out to evaluator + dispatcher + **outbox relay** so the module slots into the existing `BackgroundRunner` lifecycle in `app.go`.
- **Phase 3 HA (2026-04-17 audit)**:
  - Redis lease (`lease.go`) guards `evalRule` — `SET NX PX 60000` on `alerting:lease:<rule_id>` so only one pod evaluates a rule per tick.
  - Durable outbox (`outbox.go`) — evaluator writes to MySQL `observability.alert_outbox` on every transition; `Dispatcher` fast-path sends Slack and marks the row delivered; `OutboxRelay` polls every 15s (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`), exponential backoff on failures. Survives pod crash + webhook outage. Dedup via unique key `(alert_id, instance_key, transition_seq)`.
  - **Deferred**: the submodule structural split (`rules/`, `incidents/`, `silences/`, `slack/`, `engine/`, `shared/`) — tracked in the Phase 3 plan for a dedicated follow-up session to avoid risk of regressing the HA work above.

